This paper deals with privacy issues in important passage retrieval, which falls under the categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and data mining (cs.DS). However, the paper specifically focuses on creating secure representations of documents using hashing schemes, which is a topic related to cryptography (cs.CR). The use of binary embeddings and approximate distance computation also involves machine learning (cs.LG) and database systems (cs.DB). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.DS, and cs.DB.
